    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 5000i and 9000i - LIGHT SYSTEMS - DESCRIPTION - Work Light With
        PRO SLEEPER
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Work Light With PRO SLEEPER</title>
        <para>The work light circuit consists of two work lights, a work light switch, and an indicator light located in
            the instrument cluster. These lights are located on the back of the sleeper and provide light for the
            operator when the trailer air and electrical lines are being connected or disconnected from the trailer.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
